      <Notes><![CDATA[  A collaborative research agreement between the Peoples' Republic of China's (PRC) Chinese Academy of Sciences and the United States Department of Energy, signed in August of 1987, has resulted in the compilation and exchange of several data sets that will be useful in reconstructing past climates in China, extending and calibrating instrumental records, and addressing potential CO2-induced global and regional warming.
<br><br>
  This report describes one of the twelve PRC proxy data sets exchanged as part of this bilateral agreement.  For the Holocene period, annual and seasonal means are provided.  For the modern record, only 30 year annual means are provided.  Annual and seasonal differences between the two periods are provided for each of 52 locations.  These records may be used to compare regional climate changes in China during the Holocene period with modern climate.]]></Notes>
